.TH AEROLITCTL-BACKUP 1 "June 2026" "aerolitctl 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
aerolitctl-backup \- back up AeroLIT configuration footprint
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B aerolitctl backup config
[\fB--output-dir\fR \fIDIR\fR] [\fB--dry-run\fR] [\fB--list-files\fR]
[\fB--include-rendered\fR] [\fB--no-state\fR] [\fB--no-bundle-generated\fR]
[\fB--verbose\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B aerolitctl backup config
creates a compressed archive of AeroLIT-owned configuration and generated input
files. It backs up the configuration footprint, not the full bundle, RPM repos,
ISOs, or extracted ISO content.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --output-dir " DIR"
Directory where the backup archive should be written. The default is under
.IR /var/lib/aerolit/backups/config .
.TP
.B --dry-run
Show what would be backed up without creating an archive.
.TP
.B --list-files
List files included in the backup plan.
.TP
.B --include-rendered
Include files under
.IR /var/lib/aerolit/rendered .
.TP
.B --no-state
Do not include
.IR /var/lib/aerolit/state.yml .
.TP
.B --no-bundle-generated
Do not include AeroLIT-managed generated files from the active
.I collections-hub
bundle.
.TP
.B --verbose
Show more detailed output.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
aerolitctl backup config --dry-run --list-files
sudo aerolitctl backup config
sudo aerolitctl backup config --output-dir /var/lib/aerolit/backups/config
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/aerolit/aerolitctl.yml
Main config file included when present.
.TP
.I /etc/aerolit/overrides
Override files included when present.
.TP
.I /var/lib/aerolit/state.yml
State file included unless
.B --no-state
is supplied.
.TP
.I /var/lib/aerolit/rendered
Rendered files included only with
.BR --include-rendered .
.TP
.I <bundle>/collections-hub/ansible/group_vars/all/aerolitctl_*_generated.yml
Generated vars included unless
.B --no-bundle-generated
is supplied.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR aerolitctl (1),
.BR aerolitctl-settings (1),
.BR aerolitctl-sync (1)








.TH AEROLITCTL-BUNDLE 1 "June 2026" "aerolitctl 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
aerolitctl-bundle \- show and validate the AeroLIT offline bundle
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B aerolitctl bundle show
[\fB--path\fR \fIPATH\fR] [\fB--verbose\fR]
.br
.B aerolitctl bundle validate
[\fB--path\fR \fIPATH\fR] [\fB--verbose\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B aerolitctl bundle
inspects the configured AeroLIT bundle or a path supplied on the command line.
It is read-only.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B show
Print important bundle-derived paths and whether common locations are present.
.TP
.B validate
Validate required and expected bundle layout. The validator checks the bundle
root, manifest, 
.IR collections-hub ,
.IR collections-hub/ansible ,
.IR collections-hub/templates ,
.IR repos ,
.IR files ,
.IR extracted_isos ,
Ansible template directories, GitLab CI templates, active Ansible files, and
aerolitctl generated server variables where applicable.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --path " PATH"
Inspect or validate
.I PATH
without changing
.IR /etc/aerolit/aerolitctl.yml .
.TP
.B --verbose
Show more detailed output.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
aerolitctl bundle show
aerolitctl bundle validate
aerolitctl bundle validate --path /opt/aerolit/aerolit-bundle
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/aerolit/aerolitctl.yml
Read when
.B --path
is not supplied.
.TP
.I <bundle>/aerolit-bundle.yml
Bundle manifest, validated when present.
.TP
.I <bundle>/collections-hub
Required bundle content root.
.TP
.I <bundle>/repos
Required repository content root.
.TP
.I <bundle>/files
Required file payload root.
.TP
.I <bundle>/extracted_isos
Required extracted ISO root.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B validate
returns non-zero when required checks fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR aerolitctl (1),
.BR aerolitctl-path (1),
.BR aerolitctl-doctor (1)









.TH AEROLITCTL-CONFIGURE 1 "June 2026" "aerolitctl 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
aerolitctl-configure \- capture AeroLIT configuration answers and generated inputs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B aerolitctl configure init
[\fB--bundle\fR \fIPATH\fR] [\fB--force\fR] [\fB--dry-run\fR] [\fB--non-interactive\fR] [\fB--no-backup\fR]
.br
.B aerolitctl configure all
[\fB--guided\fR|\fB--show\fR|\fB--validate\fR|\fB--dry-run\fR|\fB--non-interactive\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.br
.B aerolitctl configure server
[\fB--guided\fR|\fB--show\fR|\fB--dry-run\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.br
.B aerolitctl configure ansible
[\fB--show\fR|\fB--guided\fR|\fB--dry-run\fR|\fB--validate\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.br
.B aerolitctl configure repos
[\fB--guided\fR|\fB--show\fR|\fB--validate\fR|\fB--refresh\fR|\fB--dry-run\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.br
.B aerolitctl configure pxe
[\fB--show\fR|\fB--guided\fR|\fB--dry-run\fR|\fB--validate\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B aerolitctl configure
writes saved answers and AeroLIT-managed generated inputs. It is the configuration
capture layer, not the deployment layer. It does not run deployment playbooks,
restart services, open firewall ports, or export NFS paths; those actions belong
to
.BR "aerolitctl deploy server" .
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B init
Create or refresh AeroLIT control directories and active bundle Ansible files
from templates. It can create
.IR collections-hub/.sync-preserve ,
.IR collections-hub/.gitlab-ci.yml ,
and active
.IR ansible.cfg ,
.IR inventory ,
and
.IR group_vars
content.
.TP
.B all
Coordinate the implemented configure sections:
.BR init ,
.BR server ,
.BR repos ,
.BR ansible ,
and
.BR pxe .
Without show, validation, dry-run, or non-interactive mode, guided mode is the
normal behavior.
.TP
.B server
Store server mode, PXE network, DHCP, interface intent, NFS intent, PXE HTTP,
and firewall-management intent for later deploy.
.TP
.B ansible
Manage aerolitctl-owned inventory and generated vars under the active bundle's
.IR collections-hub/ansible
area.
.TP
.B repos
Discover or record server and provisioning repository sources, refresh generated
repo variables, optionally write a server bootstrap repo file, and optionally
install server prerequisite packages.
.TP
.B pxe
Manage aerolitctl-owned PXE profile overrides and pxe-content generator settings.
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --bundle " PATH"
Bundle path for
.B configure init
and
.BR "configure all" .
.TP
.BI --bundle-path " PATH"
Bundle path for
.BR "configure ansible" ,
.BR "configure repos" ,
and
.BR "configure pxe" .
.TP
.B --guided
Prompt interactively for common settings.
.TP
.B --show
Show saved or planned settings without writing.
.TP
.B --validate
Run read-only validation where implemented.
.TP
.B --dry-run
Preview changes without writing files.
.TP
.B --force
Allow replacement of existing non-aerolitctl-managed output files where supported.
.TP
.B --no-backup
Do not create timestamped backups before changing managed files.
.TP
.B --verbose
Show more detailed output.
.SH SERVER OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --mode " full|pxe|controller"
Store server mode.
.TP
.BI --interface " IFACE"
Provisioning/PXE interface.
.TP
.BI --server-ip " ADDRESS"
AeroLIT server IP on the provisioning network.
.TP
.BI --network " CIDR"
Provisioning network, for example
.IR 192.168.98.0/24 .
.TP
.BI --prefix " N"
CIDR prefix length.
.TP
.BI --gateway " ADDRESS|none"
PXE gateway.
.TP
.BI --dns " LIST"
Comma-separated DNS servers.
.TP
.BI --dhcp-start " ADDRESS"
PXE DHCP range start.
.TP
.BI --dhcp-end " ADDRESS"
PXE DHCP range end.
.TP
.BI --pxe-http-port " PORT"
PXE HTTP content port.
.TP
.BI --pxe-http-bind-address " ADDRESS"
PXE HTTP bind address.
.TP
.B --configure-interface
Store intent for deploy to configure the selected interface.
.TP
.B --no-configure-interface
Store intent for deploy not to configure the selected interface.
.TP
.B --nfs-enabled
Enable controller/NFS generated settings.
.TP
.B --no-nfs
Disable controller/NFS generated settings.
.TP
.BI --nfs-export-path " PATH"
NFS export path to store for deploy.
.TP
.BI --nfs-allow-clients " CLIENTS"
Allowed NFS clients. Alias:
.BR --nfs-allowed-clients .
.TP
.B --nfs-allow-all-clients
Store intent to allow all clients.
.TP
.B --no-nfs-allow-all-clients
Store intent not to allow all clients.
.TP
.B --nfs-create-export-path
Store intent for deploy to create the export path.
.TP
.B --no-nfs-create-export-path
Store intent not to create the export path.
.TP
.BI --nfs-exports-file " PATH"
NFS exports file path for later deploy.
.TP
.BI --target-mount-path " PATH"
Client-visible mount path.
.TP
.BI --mount-mode " MODE"
Mode for generated NFS mount variables.
.TP
.BI --mount-owner " USER"
Owner for generated NFS mount variables.
.TP
.BI --mount-group " GROUP"
Group for generated NFS mount variables.
.TP
.B --firewall-manage
Store intent for deploy/roles to manage required firewall rules.
.TP
.B --no-firewall-manage
Store intent not to manage firewall rules.
.SH ANSIBLE OPTIONS
.TP
.B --ensure-standard-groups
Ensure standard AeroLIT groups exist.
.TP
.B --local-controller
Add localhost to
.B ansible_controller
and
.B pxe_server
with local connection.
.TP
.BI --add-group " GROUP"
Add or ensure a managed group. Repeatable.
.TP
.BI --remove-group " GROUP"
Remove a managed group.
.TP
.BI --add-child-group " PARENT CHILD"
Add a managed child-group relationship.
.TP
.BI --remove-child-group " PARENT CHILD"
Remove a managed child-group relationship.
.TP
.BI --add-host " HOST"
Add or ensure a managed host. Repeatable.
.TP
.BI --remove-host " HOST"
Remove a managed host from aerolitctl-managed groups.
.TP
.BI --remove-host-from-group " HOST GROUP"
Remove a managed host from one managed group.
.TP
.BI --group " GROUP"
Group for added hosts or host ranges.
.TP
.BI --ansible-host " ADDRESS"
Set
.B ansible_host
for added hosts. Alias:
.BR --ip .
.TP
.BI --ansible-user " USER"
Set
.BR ansible_user .
.TP
.BI --ansible-port " PORT"
Set
.BR ansible_port .
.TP
.BI --ssh-key " PATH"
Set
.B ansible_ssh_private_key_file
for added hosts. Alias:
.BR --private-key .
.TP
.BI --connection " TYPE"
Set
.B ansible_connection
for added hosts.
.TP
.BI --python-interpreter " PATH"
Set
.BR ansible_python_interpreter .
.TP
.B --become
Set
.B ansible_become=true
for added hosts.
.TP
.B --no-become
Set
.B ansible_become=false
for added hosts.
.TP
.BI --host-var " KEY=VALUE"
Set an extra variable for added hosts.
.TP
.BI --set-host-var " HOST KEY=VALUE"
Set a variable on an existing managed host.
.TP
.BI --remove-host-var " HOST KEY"
Remove a variable from an existing managed host.
.TP
.BI --set-global-var " KEY=VALUE"
Set a global variable in
.IR group_vars/all/aerolitctl_ansible_generated.yml .
.TP
.BI --remove-global-var " KEY"
Remove a global generated variable.
.TP
.BI --set-group-var " GROUP KEY=VALUE"
Set a group variable in
.IR group_vars/GROUP/aerolitctl.yml .
.TP
.BI --remove-group-var " GROUP KEY"
Remove a managed group variable.
.TP
.B --allow-sensitive-vars
Allow sensitive-looking variable names such as password, token, or secret.
.TP
.BI --add-host-range " PREFIX"
Add generated hosts using
.I PREFIX
and a zero-padded number.
.TP
.BI --range-start " N"
Start number for
.BR --add-host-range .
.TP
.BI --range-end " N"
End number for
.BR --add-host-range .
.TP
.BI --host-number-width " N"
Zero-padding width for generated host names. Default: 3.
.TP
.BI --ip-start " ADDRESS"
Starting IP address for generated host ranges.
.SH REPOS OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --path-for-ansible " PATH"
Client-visible bundle path used for provisioning repo baseurls. Defaults to
.IR /home/unix/sysadmin .
.TP
.B --refresh
Write generated repo variables from discovered bundle repos and explicit overrides.
.TP
.B --write-server-bootstrap
Write
.I /etc/yum.repos.d/zz-aerolit-server-bootstrap.repo
from discovered current-OS BaseOS/AppStream bundle repos.
.TP
.BI --server-bootstrap-repo-file " PATH"
Override the server bootstrap repo file path.
.TP
.B --ensure-server-prereqs
Ensure server prerequisite packages are installed.
.TP
.BI --server-prereq-package " PACKAGE"
Override prerequisite packages. Repeatable.
.TP
.B --server-bootstrap-only
For prerequisite handling, skip existing enabled repos and use only
aerolit-server-bootstrap repositories.
.TP
.BI --server-baseos-source " PATH_OR_URL"
Explicit BaseOS source for server bootstrap packages.
.TP
.BI --server-appstream-source " PATH_OR_URL"
Explicit AppStream source for server bootstrap packages.
.TP
.BI --provision-repo " OS:ID=PATH_OR_URL"
Add an explicit provisioning repo override. Repeatable.
.TP
.BI --provision-extra-repo " OS:ID=PATH_OR_URL"
Alias-style extra provisioning repo override. Repeatable.
.TP
.B --no-auto-discovery
Do not automatically scan the bundle for repos. Alias:
.BR --disable-auto-discovery .
.SH PXE OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --enable-profile " PROFILE"
Show a PXE profile in the generated boot menu. Repeatable.
.TP
.BI --disable-profile " PROFILE"
Hide a PXE profile from the generated boot menu. Repeatable.
.TP
.BI --remove-profile " PROFILE"
Remove a custom aerolitctl-managed PXE profile override.
.TP
.BI --implement-profile " PROFILE"
Mark a profile implemented so real boot targets/Kickstarts are generated.
.TP
.BI --placeholder-profile " PROFILE"
Mark a profile as a placeholder.
.TP
.BI --set-profile-title " PROFILE TITLE"
Set profile display title.
.TP
.BI --set-profile-label " PROFILE LABEL"
Set install label.
.TP
.BI --set-profile-menu-target " PROFILE TARGET"
Set iPXE menu target.
.TP
.BI --set-profile-template " PROFILE TEMPLATE"
Set Kickstart template path.
.TP
.BI --set-profile-os " PROFILE OS_LIST"
Set comma-separated supported OS IDs.
.TP
.BI --set-profile-kernel-args " PROFILE ARGS"
Set comma-separated extra kernel args.
.TP
.BI --profile-uefi " PROFILE"
Enable UEFI menu entries.
.TP
.BI --no-profile-uefi " PROFILE"
Disable UEFI menu entries.
.TP
.BI --profile-bios " PROFILE"
Enable BIOS/legacy menu entries.
.TP
.BI --no-profile-bios " PROFILE"
Disable BIOS/legacy menu entries.
.TP
.BI --watch-interval " SECONDS"
PXE content generator watch interval.
.TP
.BI --generated-ks-edit-policy " preserve|overwrite"
Policy for generated Kickstarts when manual edits are detected.
.TP
.BI --validation-failure-policy " warn|fail"
PXE content validation failure policy.
.TP
.B --reset-standard-profiles
Reset managed PXE profiles to AeroLIT standard defaults.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
sudo aerolitctl configure init --bundle /opt/aerolit/aerolit-bundle
aerolitctl configure all --guided
aerolitctl configure server --guided
aerolitctl configure server --mode full --interface ens160 --server-ip 192.168.98.10 --network 192.168.98.0/24
aerolitctl configure ansible --local-controller --ensure-standard-groups
aerolitctl configure repos --show
sudo aerolitctl configure repos --ensure-server-prereqs
aerolitctl configure pxe --validate
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/aerolit/aerolitctl.yml
Saved configuration read and written by configure commands.
.TP
.I /etc/yum.repos.d/zz-aerolit-server-bootstrap.repo
Optional server bootstrap repo file written by
.BR "configure repos" .
.TP
.I <bundle>/collections-hub/ansible/inventory/90_aerolitctl.ini
Managed inventory fragment.
.TP
.I <bundle>/collections-hub/ansible/group_vars/all/aerolitctl_ansible_generated.yml
Managed Ansible generated variables.
.TP
.I <bundle>/collections-hub/ansible/group_vars/all/aerolitctl_server_generated.yml
Managed server generated variables.
.TP
.I <bundle>/collections-hub/ansible/group_vars/all/aerolitctl_repos_generated.yml
Managed repository generated variables.
.TP
.I <bundle>/collections-hub/ansible/group_vars/all/aerolitctl_pxe_generated.yml
Managed PXE generated variables.
.TP
.I /etc/aerolit/overrides/pxe/profiles
Managed PXE profile overrides.
.SH NOTES
Use
.B deploy server
after reviewing saved intent. Configuration files are inputs to deployment; they
are not proof that services have already been changed.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR aerolitctl (1),
.BR aerolitctl-deploy (1),
.BR aerolitctl-generate (1),
.BR aerolitctl-settings (1)







.TH AEROLITCTL-DEPLOY 1 "June 2026" "aerolitctl 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
aerolitctl-deploy \- apply saved AeroLIT server configuration
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B aerolitctl deploy server
[\fB--dry-run\fR] [\fB--show\fR] [\fB--skip-interface\fR] [\fB--skip-nfs\fR]
[\fB--skip-firewall\fR] [\fB--skip-pxe\fR] [\fB--skip-controller\fR]
[\fB--skip-repo-prep\fR] [\fB--skip-server-prereqs\fR]
[\fB--skip-repo-vars-refresh\fR] [\fB--server-bootstrap-only\fR] [\fB--verbose\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B aerolitctl deploy
performs deployment actions from saved configuration. In this build the
implemented target is
.BR server .
.PP
.B deploy server
builds a plan from
.IR /etc/aerolit/aerolitctl.yml ,
prepares repository inputs unless skipped, refreshes generated server variables,
and invokes the configured PXE server and/or Ansible controller playbooks from
the active bundle when enabled.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --dry-run
Show what would happen without changing files or services.
.TP
.B --show
Show the saved deploy plan without changing anything.
.TP
.B --skip-interface
Do not apply NetworkManager interface IP changes.
.TP
.B --skip-nfs
Do not create or update NFS exports, permissions, or NFS services.
.TP
.B --skip-firewall
Disable role-level firewall management for this deploy run.
.TP
.B --skip-pxe
Do not run the PXE server playbook.
.TP
.B --skip-controller
Do not run the Ansible controller playbook.
.TP
.B --skip-repo-prep
Skip automatic repository preparation, including server prerequisite handling and
generated provisioning repo vars refresh.
.TP
.B --skip-server-prereqs
Do not automatically install missing server prerequisite packages.
.TP
.B --skip-repo-vars-refresh
Do not automatically refresh
.IR collections-hub/ansible/group_vars/all/aerolitctl_repos_generated.yml .
.TP
.B --server-bootstrap-only
For prerequisite handling, skip existing enabled repos and use only
aerolit-server-bootstrap repositories.
.TP
.B --verbose
Show more detailed output.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
sudo aerolitctl deploy server --show
sudo aerolitctl deploy server --dry-run
sudo aerolitctl deploy server
sudo aerolitctl deploy server --skip-interface --skip-firewall
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/aerolit/aerolitctl.yml
Saved deployment intent.
.TP
.I /etc/yum.repos.d/zz-aerolit-server-bootstrap.repo
May be written or used during server prerequisite handling.
.TP
.I <bundle>/collections-hub/ansible/group_vars/all/aerolitctl_server_generated.yml
Generated server variables consumed by deployment playbooks.
.TP
.I <bundle>/collections-hub/ansible/group_vars/all/aerolitctl_repos_generated.yml
Generated repository variables, unless repo refresh is skipped.
.TP
.I <bundle>/collections-hub/ansible/pxe_server.yml
PXE server playbook.
.TP
.I <bundle>/collections-hub/ansible/ansible_controller.yml
Ansible controller playbook.
.SH SECURITY
This command may require root and may invoke Ansible roles that configure
interfaces, repositories, NFS, firewall behavior, PXE services, or controller
state. Review
.B --show
or
.B --dry-run
output first on production systems.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR aerolitctl (1),
.BR aerolitctl-configure (1),
.BR aerolitctl-provision (1),
.BR aerolitctl-status (1)








.TH AEROLITCTL-DOCTOR 1 "June 2026" "aerolitctl 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
aerolitctl-doctor \- run AeroLIT health checks
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B aerolitctl doctor
[\fB--verbose\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B aerolitctl doctor
runs read-oriented health checks for the local AeroLIT control environment. It
checks Python and YAML support, current privileges, configured bundle path,
important bundle directories and templates, Ansible files, playbooks, generated
server vars, PXE state, SELinux status, firewalld status, command availability
where relevant, and saved deployment readiness.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --verbose
Show more detailed output.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
aerolitctl doctor
sudo aerolitctl doctor --verbose
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/aerolit/aerolitctl.yml
Saved configuration checked by doctor.
.TP
.I /var/lib/aerolit/state.yml
State file checked when present.
.TP
.I <bundle>/collections-hub/ansible
Ansible directory checked by doctor.
.TP
.I <bundle>/collections-hub/ansible/group_vars/all
Generated variables checked by doctor.
.TP
.I /etc/aerolit/overrides/pxe
PXE override state checked by doctor.
.SH NOTES
Doctor is intended as a safe diagnostic command. It reports findings and returns
non-zero when blocking failures are found.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR aerolitctl (1),
.BR aerolitctl-status (1),
.BR aerolitctl-bundle (1)





.TH AEROLITCTL-GENERATE 1 "June 2026" "aerolitctl 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
aerolitctl-generate \- generate AeroLIT-managed playbooks and PXE/Kickstart inputs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B aerolitctl generate playbook
[\fINAME\fR] [\fB--role\fR \fIROLE\fR...] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.br
.B aerolitctl generate kickstart
[\fIPROFILE\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.br
.B aerolitctl generate pxe-profile
[\fIPROFILE\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B aerolitctl generate
creates AeroLIT-managed input files. It does not run Ansible, deploy services,
restart containers, render final boot menus, configure NFS, or change firewall
rules.
.PP
.B playbook
writes generated Ansible playbooks under the active bundle's
.IR collections-hub/ansible
directory.
.B kickstart
and its alias
.B pxe-profile
write PXE profile and Kickstart template override inputs consumed later by the
pxe-content generator.
.SH PLAYBOOK OPTIONS
.TP
.I NAME
Safe generated playbook name. Optional with
.B --guided
or
.BR --list-playbook-roles .
.TP
.B --guided
Interactively discover bundle collection roles and build a playbook.
.TP
.B --guided-show-role-details
Show role README/meta/tasks details during guided selection.
.TP
.B --list-playbook-roles
List discovered role-capable collections and roles, then exit.
.TP
.BI --collection-root " PATH"
Extra Ansible collection root to scan. Repeatable.
.TP
.BI --role " ROLE"
Role name or fully qualified collection role name. Repeatable or comma-separated.
Required unless guided mode or role listing is used.
.TP
.BI --role-order " ROLE_LIST"
Explicit final role execution order. It must contain exactly the same roles as
.BR --role .
.TP
.B --skip-role-order-review
In guided mode, skip the final role order review prompt.
.TP
.BI --hosts " PATTERN"
Ansible hosts pattern. Default:
.BR all .
.TP
.BI --title " TITLE"
Human-readable play name.
.TP
.BI --var " KEY=VALUE"
Play-level variable. Repeatable.
.TP
.BI --output " FILE"
Generated playbook filename relative to
.IR collections-hub/ansible .
.TP
.BI --bundle-path " PATH"
