.TH AEROLITCTL 1 "June 2026" "aerolitctl 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
aerolitctl \- command and control interface for offline AeroLIT bundles
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B aerolitctl
[\fB--verbose\fR]
.I COMMAND
[\fIARGS...\fR]
.br
.B aerolitctl
\fB--help\fR
.br
.B aerolitctl
.I COMMAND
\fB--help\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B aerolitctl
coordinates an AeroLIT automation bundle on RHEL 8, RHEL 9, and RHEL 10 systems.
It records local configuration intent, validates the offline bundle layout,
generates AeroLIT-owned Ansible and PXE/Kickstart inputs, runs deployment
workflows, invokes provisioning playbooks, synchronizes bundle updates, and
reports status and diagnostics.
.PP
The configured bundle path is stored in
.IR /etc/aerolit/aerolitctl.yml .
When no bundle path has been saved, commands that need a bundle normally fall
back to
.IR /opt/aerolit/aerolit-bundle
or ask the user to run
.BR "aerolitctl path set" .
.PP
.B configure
commands write saved answers and generated input files. They do not deploy
services by themselves.
.B generate
commands create playbooks and PXE/Kickstart generator inputs. They do not run
Ansible.
.B deploy
and
.B provision
commands may change local system state or remote hosts by invoking system setup
logic or Ansible.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B path
Show or update the configured AeroLIT bundle path.
.TP
.B bundle
Show or validate the configured AeroLIT bundle layout.
.TP
.B configure
Capture AeroLIT answers and write AeroLIT-managed configuration inputs.
.TP
.B generate
Generate AeroLIT-managed Ansible playbooks and PXE/Kickstart profile inputs.
.TP
.B deploy
Apply saved AeroLIT server, network, NFS, PXE, controller, and repo-prep intent.
.TP
.B provision
Run
.B ansible-playbook
from the active bundle's
.I collections-hub/ansible
directory.
.TP
.B sync
Safely sync bundle updates into sections such as
.IR collections-hub ,
.IR files ,
.IR repos ,
and
.IR extracted_isos .
.TP
.B doctor
Run health checks for the host, config file, bundle, Ansible inputs, and PXE state.
.TP
.B status
Show saved configuration and deployment readiness.
.TP
.B logs
Show command logs under the AeroLIT log directory.
.TP
.B settings
Show, export, or import saved AeroLIT settings.
.TP
.B backup
Back up AeroLIT config, state, override, and generated input files.
.TP
.B shell
Show shell integration and bash completion setup information.
.TP
.B version
Print the aerolitctl version.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, --help
Show help and exit.
.TP
.B --verbose
Show more detailed output. Leaf commands also accept
.B --verbose
where implemented.
.SH WORKFLOW
A common first-run workflow is:
.PP
.nf
aerolitctl path set /opt/aerolit/aerolit-bundle
aerolitctl bundle validate
aerolitctl configure init
aerolitctl configure all --guided
aerolitctl generate playbook deploy_pxe_content --role aerolit.example.role
aerolitctl generate kickstart --guided
sudo aerolitctl deploy server
aerolitctl provision check
aerolitctl doctor
.fi
.PP
Use
.B configure all
to coordinate configuration capture. Use
.B deploy server
to apply saved server-side intent. These commands are intentionally not the
same operation.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/aerolit/aerolitctl.yml
Main saved aerolitctl configuration.
.TP
.I /etc/aerolit/overrides/pxe/profiles
Host-side aerolitctl-managed PXE profile override files.
.TP
.I /etc/aerolit/overrides/pxe/templates
Host-side PXE template override files copied or composed by generation commands.
.TP
.I /opt/aerolit/aerolit-bundle
Default AeroLIT bundle path.
.TP
.I <bundle>/collections-hub/ansible
Active Ansible working directory used by generated playbooks and provisioning.
.TP
.I <bundle>/collections-hub/ansible/group_vars/all
Location for aerolitctl-generated Ansible input files.
.TP
.I <bundle>/collections-hub/.sync-preserve
Preserve rules used by bundle sync.
.TP
.I <bundle>/repos
Bundle repository content.
.TP
.I <bundle>/files
Bundle file payload content.
.TP
.I <bundle>/extracted_isos
Extracted RHEL ISO content used by offline workflows.
.TP
.I /var/lib/aerolit
State, backups, rendered files, and sync metadata.
.TP
.I /var/log/aerolit
Default command log directory.
.SH SECURITY
Commands that only show status, help, logs, settings, or bundle information can
usually be run as an unprivileged user if the files are readable.
Commands that write
.IR /etc/aerolit ,
.IR /etc/yum.repos.d ,
sync state under
.IR /var/lib/aerolit ,
or run deployment/provisioning actions may require root.
.PP
Command logs redact values for sensitive-looking CLI option names such as
password, token, secret, credential, and private-key.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
The command completed successfully.
.TP
.B 1
The command found a failure, validation error, missing required state, or runtime error.
.TP
.B 2
Command-line usage was invalid or a required command argument was missing.
.TP
.B 127
An external command required by the selected workflow was not found.
.TP
.B 130
The command was interrupted.
.SH NOTES
This build has no top-level repository-management or UI command. Repository
setup is handled by
.BR "aerolitctl configure repos" .
